HEADWORD: Subordinacy
<hw>Sub*or"di*na*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Subordinate</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
subordinate, or subject to control; subordination, <as>as, to bring the
imagination to act in <ex>subordinacy</ex> to reason</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
